The reward given to those who have already earned planar flags seems appropriate. Namely, a nice Charm slot item with stats that vary based upon your class and an Alternate Advancement point worth of exp for each planar flag you have. Over on the ranger board, someone on Test reported the details:<br>
<br>
This charm ramps up depending on how many PoP zones you are flagged for.<br>
<br>
If you have no flags, the charm will have no stats.<br>
<br>
My charm was this:<br>
<br>
Intricate Wooden Figurine<br>
Slot: Charm<br>
AC 5<br>
Dex 4<br>
Wis 3<br>
Agi 4<br>
HP 27<br>
Mana 24<br>
ALL RESISTS 3<br>
Wt 0.1<br>
Class: RNG (Its dependant on your class, Rogues charms wont have Mana and have different ammounts etc)<br>
<br>
I asked an elemental flagged ranger (Thank you, Cloudwraite) what his stats were (He had all flags except Time):<br>
<br>
AC 15<br>
Dex 13<br>
Sta 9<br>
Wis 9<br>
Agi 13<br>
HP 81<br>
Mana 72<br>
ALL RESISTS 9<br>
